oracle.pg.rdbms.index.jdbc

Class JdbcFileEntrySettings

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.pg.rdbms.index.jdbc.JdbcFileEntrySettings

  • public class JdbcFileEntrySettings
extends java.lang.Object
    An Oracle extension of Apache Compass JdbcFileEntrySettings to support file entry level settings over the Oracle JDBC directory. This modification supports Apache Lucene 4.0 to date. A file entry level settings is an abstract view of any type of setting that can be used by the actual file entry handler that uses it.

    Holds the FILE_ENTRY_HANDLER_TYPE that defines the type of the FileEntryHandler that will be created and initialized with the settings.

    Default values for a new instance are: FileEntryHandler for the FILE_ENTRY_HANDLER_TYPE setting, FetchOnBufferReadJdbcIndexInput for the INDEX_INPUT_TYPE_SETTING setting, and RAMAndFileJdbcIndexOutput for the INDEX_OUTPUT_TYPE_SETTING setting.
